100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 6, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and the need for collective security. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified as various states reported increasing lawlessness associated with the illegal liquor trade. Meanwhile, in the world of science, the discovery of ancient human fossils in Java continued to spark discussions about human evolution and the origins of man.
